cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the numerical linear algebra aspects of deep neural networks, specifically the Hessian matrix. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the dynamics of training and sample size, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deepnets for computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which are also possible sub-categories.
